Backend Slug/Header Dependencies

Core slug/header resolution coupling:

1) Tenant resolver and pipeline
- src/NovaNode.Api/Middleware/TenantResolutionMiddleware.cs (InvokeAsync)
  Exact behavior:
  - Reads X-Tenant-Slug request header.
  - Exempt prefixes skip resolution: /api/v1/platform, /api/v1/stores, /swagger, /uploads, /health.
  - Optional prefix: /api/v1/public (if header missing, continue unresolved).
  - Looks up tenant by Tenants.Slug.
  - Sets ITenantContext with tenant.Id and tenant.Slug.
  Conceptual change for host/domain model:
  - Resolve tenant from host/domain first (possibly fallback header during transition).
  - Replace slug-only lookup with domain mapping lookup.
  - Preserve optional/exempt semantics where needed.

- src/NovaNode.Api/Program.cs
  Exact behavior:
  - Middleware order: TenantResolution -> SubscriptionEnforcement -> GlobalException -> Authentication -> TenantClaimValidation -> Authorization.
  Conceptual change for host/domain model:
  - Same order can remain, but resolver internals change from header/slug to host/domain resolution.

2) Claim isolation bound to resolved tenant context
