Risk Classification

Low-risk migration items
- Platform-only routing and auth paths under /superadmin and /api/v1/platform.
- Generic tenant-scoped business services/controllers that consume tenantId from ITenantContext (if resolver changes are isolated and compatible).
- Static infra endpoints (/health, swagger, uploads) unaffected by tenant routing model.

Medium-risk migration items
- Storefront route rebasing for non-admin pages (catalog/item/category/brand/about/policies/compare).
- PWA manifest start_url/scope generation currently based on /store/{slug}.
- Landing tenant discovery flow currently slug-path navigation.
- Documentation set contains mixed path/query/subdomain narratives; operational confusion risk.

High-risk migration items
- Tenant identity resolution boundary: TenantResolutionMiddleware currently slug-header only.
- Frontend auth/guard/interceptor coupling to /store/:slug and stored slug redirects.
- Tenant URL generation centrality in TenantService.storeUrl/adminUrl used across many templates/components.
- Platform tenant detail/create pages currently generate stale query-param URLs and credential messages.
- API contract assumptions that X-Tenant-Slug is the required tenant context carrier for most tenant endpoints.

Unknowns requiring Phase 3 investigation
- Canonical future host model details:
  - single primary domain per tenant vs multiple domains
  - precedence between subdomain and custom domain if both exist
  - fallback behavior when domain not verified
- Backward compatibility requirements:
  - whether /store/:slug routes must continue to work during transition window
  - whether X-Tenant-Slug header remains supported temporarily
- Domain ownership verification process design and operational requirements (DNS/TXT/CNAME/HTTP challenge).
- Cross-origin and cookie/session implications if tenant domains differ from platform domain.
- SEO/link migration requirements and redirects from old path URLs to domain URLs.


